<%= content_tag(:div, '', id: 'front') unless mobile_device? %>
<%= hidden_field_tag(:base_rate, base_rate) %>
<%= hidden_field_tag(:tax_rate, tax_rate) %>
<%= hidden_field_tag(:main_pic_url, asset_path('front-main.jpg')) %>
<div class="wrapper medium">
  <h2 class="c light-gray" style="margin-top: 0;">
    Welcome to Hana's Tradewind Cottage
  </h2>

  <p>
    As you follow the private drive through the tropical flower garden to our
    secluded Tradewinds Cottage, you will
    discover the Hawaii that you came to see.
  </p>

  <p>
    Surrounded by exotic flowers and tropical fruit trees, our two bedroom, one bath cottage has <b>Wi-Fi</b>,
    <b>cable TV</b>, <b>DVD and CD stereo</b>. There is a gas cook top, refrigerator and microwave oven in the
    newly remodeled kitchen with a propane barbeque outside on the covered deck.
  </p>

  <p>
    The cottage has a queen size bed, two twin beds and a queen size sleeper sofa. You'll enjoy the splendor of the
    slopes of Haleakala while relaxing in your private hot tub or cooking your favorite island-style feast on the
    barbeque under your covered lanai.
  </p>
</div>

<%= section_header('Reservations') %>

<div class="wrapper medium-minor mb20">
  <p class="medium">
    Planning a trip to the east side of Maui? Be sure to book your stay with us as early as possible.
    We are usually booked months in advance.
  </p>

  <h4>Rates</h4>
  <ul class="pad medium-minor">
    <li>Base rate is $<%= base_rate %></li>
    <li>Nightly rate for <%= text_field_tag(:people_count, 2, class: 'instep', maxlength: 2) %> people
      <span>+<%= tax_rate * 100 %>% tax</span> =
      <span class="bold" id="rate_result">$<%= ((tax_rate + 1) * base_rate.to_f).round(2) %></span></li>
    <li>The cottage can accommodate a <b>maximum of 4 guests</b>. <b>No pets.</b></li>
    <li><b>Note:</b> There is a charge of $25 per night for each additional person.</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Availability</h4>

  <p class="medium">
    Our next opening is <span class="green"><%= @availability.start_at.to_formatted_s(:long) %></span>
    for <%= pluralize(@availability.duration, 'night') %>. <%= @availability.error %>
  </p>

  <p class="medium">
    Check availability for your trip by entering your arrival and departure date below. Optionally, you can
    <a href="javascript:;" id="view_entire_calendar" class="linked">view the calendar</a>.
  </p>

  <div id="error_box" class="alert alert-block alert-error fade" style="display: none;">
    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert">&times;</button>
    <p class="error-message" style="margin: 3px;"></p>
  </div>
  <div class="pl20 no-pad-mobile">
    <%= form_tag(calendar_create_path, remote: true, id: 'check_avail') do %>
        <table class="basic w600">
          <tr>
            <td style="width: 120px"><label for="arrival_date_r">Arrival date</label></td>
            <td><%= text_field_tag(:arrival_date, @availability.start_at.strftime('%m/%d/%Y'), placeholder: 'Arrival date', id: 'arrival_date_r', class: 'dp') %></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><label for="departure_date_r">Departure date</label></td>
            <td><%= text_field_tag(:departure_date, (@availability.start_at + 2.days).strftime('%m/%d/%Y'), placeholder: 'Departure date', id: 'departure_date_r', class: 'dp') %></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td></td>
            <td>
              <div class="fl">
                <%= submit_tag('Check Availability', disable_with: 'Checking ...') %>
              </div>
              <div class="fl pt4">
                <span class="available">Available! <a href="#contact" class="send_inquiry linked">Submit an
                  inquiry</a></span>
            <span class="unavailable">Unavailable.<i style="color:#666"> Try our sister site
              <a href="http://hanamaui.net" class="linked">hanamaui.net</a></i></span>
              </div>
              <div style="clear:both"></div>
            </td>
          </tr>
        </table>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  <%= hidden_field_tag(:vrbo_calendar_url, VRBO::Calendar.url) %>
  <div id="iframe_ph"></div>

  <h4>Reservation Policies</h4>

  <ul class="pad medium-minor">
    <li>
      <b>Minimum stay:</b> We have a two night minimum stay for all reservations made more than a week in advance,
      except when there is an open night “sandwiched” between two existing reservations. We are happy to accept one
      night stays 7 days in advance. There will be a $25 cleaning fee for a one night reservation for two people and
      a $35 cleaning fee for three or four people who stay for only one night.
    </li>

    <li>
      <b>Deposits:</b> A 25% deposit is required to reserve the cottage and the balance is due 30 days in advance.
    </li>

    <li style="margin-top: -15px;">
      <b>Payment:</b> We accept Visa, MasterCard, American Express and Discover.
      <span><%= image_tag(asset_path('visa_mastercard_american_express_discover.png'), style: 'position: relative;top: 13px;') %></span>
    </li>

    <li>
      <b>Check-in:</b> <br/>
      Check-in time is 3:00 p.m. <br/>
      Check-out time is 11:00 a.m.
    </li>

    <li>
      <b>Cancellation:</b>
      We will refund your deposit less a 10% cancellation fee if you notify us
      <span class="medium bold">30 days prior to you arrival</span>.
      Cancellations within 30 days of your arrival will be refunded only for the nights we are able to re-book the
      accommodations minus a 10% service fee.
      <p>
        If you check out prior to your scheduled check out date we will refund only for the nights we are able to
        re-book
        the accommodations minus a 10% service fee.
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <b>Laundry facilities</b> are available free of charge for guests staying 5 or more nights.
    </li>

    <li>
      <b>Special Terms:</b> <br/>
      Rates and policies are subject to change.<br/>
      To provide a smoke free environment for our guests, smoking is only allowed outside. <br/>
      No pets are allowed at the cottage.<br/>

      <p><a href="#contact" class="linked">Make a reservation inquiry.</a></p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>
<%= section_header('Photos') %>
<div class="wrapper medium-minor" id="photos_section">
  <% if mobile_device? %>
      <p>
        It looks like you're mobile, so we didn't load the pictures right
        away. <%= link_to('Load photos now!', 'javascript:;', class: 'linked', id: 'load_photos') %>
      </p>

      <div id="gallery_ph"></div>
  <% else %>
      <div id="gallery_ontainer" style="height: 615px;">
        <%= render('photos') %>
      </div>
  <% end %>
</div>
<%= section_header('Contact') %>
<div class="wrapper medium-minor">
  <div class="fl w49">
    <p class="form-text">
      Submit a reservation inquiry using the form below.
    </p>

    <div id="form_success_box" class="alert alert-info" style="display: none;">
      <b>Success!</b> We've received your inquiry and will get back to you at our earliest convenience.
    </div>
    <div id="form_error_box" class="alert alert-block alert-error fade" style="display: none;">
      <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="alert">&times;</button>
      <h4 class="alert-heading">Oops!</h4>

      <p class="error-message"></p>
    </div>
    <div class="pad10 no-pad-mobile">
      <%= render('contact/form') %>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="fr w49">
    <p>
      Need help right away? Contact us directly.
    </p>

    <div class="pad10">
      <p class="medium-major">
        Phone: (808) 248-8980 <br/>
        Toll Free: 1-800-327-8097
      </p>

      <p class="medium-major">
        Email: <a href="mailto:brianna@tradewindscottage.net" class="linked">brianna@tradewindscottage.net</a>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <%= image_tag(asset_path('hamoa_overview.png'), width: '310') %>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<%= section_header('Hana') %>
<div class="wrapper medium-minor">
  <p class="medium">
    Hana is a small town located on the <b>east side of Maui</b>. It is home to some of the
    <a href="http://xfinity.comcast.net/slideshow/news-bestbeaches/7/" target="_blank" class="linked">
      world’s most beautiful beaches</a>,
    breath taking waterfalls, and majestic coastlines. From Kahului airport it is about a 50 mile drive along the
    winding coastline. Along the way you can enjoy hiking trails, beautiful overlooks, and incredible waterfalls.
  </p>

  <p>
    Hana town is limited when it comes to night life and dining options. There is one gas station and two small
    stores (<b>closes at 7:30 PM</b>). If you are staying for several nights, we recommend buying groceries in Kahului
    before driving to Hana. Travaasa Hotel has a bar and restaurant, although it is a bit pricey, and so does
    the Hana Ranch Restaurant (also pricey). There are a several locally owned eateries and lunch
    wagons around town. A local favorite is
    <a href="http://www.yelp.com/biz/thai-food-by-pranee-hana" target="_blank" class="linked" title="view Pranee's on Yelp">Pranee's</a>,
    which has excellent Thai food. Checkout
    <a href="http://www.yelp.com/search?find_desc=&find_loc=H%C4%81na%2C+HI&ns=1&ls=2b7c66da1def68e9" target="_blank" class="linked">Hana
      on Yelp</a>
    for a list of popular activities and food options.
  </p>

  <p>
    There are a variety of outdoor activities, some of which we’ve listed below. It is nice to have a couple of days to
    spend in Hana because it is a long trip out here. That way you have some time to just relax and explore this side of
    the island.
  </p>

  <p>
    For more information on Hana please visit
    <a target="_blank" href="http://www.hanamaui.com" class="linked">hanamaui.com</a>
  </p>
  <h4>Activities</h4>
  <ul class="pad">
    <li>Go hang gliding down the road (1 minute away):
      <a target="_blank" href="http://www.hangglidingmaui.com" class="linked">hangglidingmaui.com</a></li>
    <li>Spelunking in lava tube (2 minutes away):
      <a target="_blank" href="http://www.mauicave.com" class="linked">mauicave.com</a>
    </li>
    <li>Go kayaking, snorkeling, surfing, or free diving (10 minutes away):
      <a target="_blank" href="http://www.hanabaykayaks.com" class="linked">hanabaykayaks.com</a></li>
    <li>Guided hike and taro patch tour at Kapahu Living Farm (45 minutes away):
      <a target="_blank" href="http://kipahulu.org/hike.html" class="linked">kipahulu.org/hike.html</a></li>
    <li>Ohe’o (7 Sacred Pools) and bamboo forest (45 minutes away):
      <a target="_blank" href="http://www.nps.gov/hale/index.htm" class="linked">nps.gov/hale/</a></li>
    <li>Horse back riding (45 minutes away):
      <a target="_blank" href="http://www.mauistables.com" class="linked">mauistables.com</a>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <h4>Location</h4>

  <p>The map below shows the route from the Kahului Airport (OGG) to the Tradewind Cottage (Approximately 52 miles).</p>
  <% unless Rails.env.development? %>
      <iframe src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m29!1m12!1m3!1d238610.7238657256!2d-156.3722470141209!3d20.860254975716938!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!4m14!1i0!3e6!4m5!1s0x7954d2b01b8e0419%3A0xc35ea962dd1a9041!2sKahului+Airport%2C+1+Kahului+Airport+Rd%2C+Kahului%2C+HI+96732!3m2!1d20.896791999999998!2d-156.43293799999998!4m5!1s0x7954ada37cc29da1%3A0xb9089f2ff788b1df!2sHana&#39;s+Tradewind+Cottages%2C+135+Alalele+Rd%2C+Hana%2C+HI+96713!3m2!1d20.790406!2d-156.01775899999998!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1394938868443" width="100%" height="450" frameborder="0" style="border:0"></iframe>
  <% end %>

</div>